      "span_text": "In a subgroup analysis from the PREVENT IV study, in which all patients received aspirin at hospital discharge, clopidogrel use was associated with a trend for higher rates of occluded vein grafts during 12-18 months (49% vs. 39%; adjusted odds ratio 1.26; P=0.08) and with similar composite rates of death, myocardial infarction, or revascularization (27% vs. 24%; adjusted HR 1.10; P=0.38) in 5 years compared with those without it"
